Look, if you must know about this particular Vietnamese poet, let's get it over with. And for the record, if you’re searching for the 16th-century author of *Strange Tales*, you've stumbled into the wrong century. That would be [Nguyễn Dữ](/Nguy%E1%BB%85n_D%E1%BB%AF). Try to keep up.

A necessary clarification for those who struggle with the basics: in this [Vietnamese name](/Vietnamese_name), the [surname](/Surname) is Nguyễn, which you've likely seen simplified to "Nguyen" in your English-centric corner of the world. However, according to Vietnamese custom, you refer to him by his [given name](/Given_name), Du. Commit that to memory. Or don't. The universe is indifferent.

